    "question": "Problem 11.3. Show that a system's intrinsic spin 4-vector $\\mathbf{S}_{\\alpha}$ is orthogonal to its 4-velocity $\\mathbf{u}^{\\alpha}$ .",
    "answer": "$\\\\mathbf{u}^{\\\\alpha} \\\\mathbf{S}_{\\\\alpha} = 0$",
    "solution": "Solution 11.3. From the definition of $S_{a}$ ,\\n$$\\n\\\\mathsf {u}^{\\\\alpha} \\\\mathsf {S}_{\\\\alpha} = - \\\\frac {1}{2} \\\\varepsilon_{\\\\alpha \\\\beta \\\\gamma \\\\delta} \\\\mathsf {J}^{\\\\beta \\\\gamma} \\\\mathsf {u}^{\\\\delta} \\\\mathsf {u}^{\\\\alpha} = 0\\n$$\\nby antisymmetry of $\\\\varepsilon$ and symmetry of $\\\\mathfrak{u}^{\\\\delta}\\\\mathfrak{u}^{a}$"
